26492,My evening scent for today is Wood Sage & Sea Salt by Jenny Glow (a brand under @sterlingparfumsuae, which is also the maker of @armafuae). This is obviously an impression of Jo Malone’s famous scent with the same name. I have tried the original and I’d say Jenny Glow’s version is 95% similar. I love this scent; it is clean, airy and “crispy”, just like ocean breeze. My problem with Jo Malone is the performance/longevity and seems like Jenny Glow’s version fixes that problem. I got 80ml bottle of this for under 30 dollars from @fragrancebuy and it came with a huge scented candle in a nice gift box! Talk about value buy! 🤩 Now I’m curious to try more scents from Jenny Glow! 😍🤩❤️

26192,HOW I EAT WHEN I TRAVEL 🥤 I think everyone has this crazy idea in their head that I eat healthy ALL of the time. Let me be the first to tell you, that is not true!! And DEFINITELY not true when it comes to what I eat when I travel ✈️ - I never ever want to feel limited when I’m traveling and trying new places (or ever really). Of course, I am aware of when I need to fuel my body with healthier foods but I think some people would be shocked to know I do not have ANY rules when it comes to how I eat when I travel. In my opinion - food is an incredible way to get to know a place and enjoy it. Healthy options are amazing and I had some this time around in NYC - but, I am also a lover of fries, pizza, milkshakes, soda etc. I know some fitness professionals may shriek at the idea of soda and to be honest I didn’t drink it for a long time (or at least the real stuff) but I love me some carbonated coke 😋 sometimes I feel that because of my career I have to hide that. Why? It makes me less fit? Nah, I think it makes me more human to own up to it. I just want to keep it real with you guys. - I am just living my life and making choices that make me happy and feel balanced. Eat the pizza, drink the soda, indulge in all the foods — if it feels right to you. And get back into your routine when you’re home. ps don’t forget: even when you’re not traveling - balance is a good thing 🍟☺️ xx
